Juliana Covarrubias is a graduate student in the Mechanical Engineering department at UC Berkeley. Her main research interests are in tangible human-computer interaction and creating meaningful relationships with technology through design. She graduated with a BS in Mechanical Engineering and Art & Design from MIT. In her free time, she enjoys taking the train and making little things.
